$ VBA Module Text [Common]

The function `regexpSplit` splits a given input string on a → development/languages/JavaScript/objects/String/regular-expression[regular expression].
(See also → development/languages/VBA/regular-expressions[regular expressions in VBA]).

`rpad` and `lpad` pads a string on the left or right side with spaces, or optionally any other character.

`parsePossibleDate` is a (very β) attempt to parse → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/string[strings] (more correctly:
a → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/variant[variant]) that might contain dates and if matched, return
such a → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/date[date]. If the value could not be mached, it returns
→ development/languages/VBA/functions/conversion/cDate[`cvDate(null)`].

